1
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:23,375
This place is...

2
00:00:23,458 --> 00:00:24,666
[BLOIS]
That's right.

3
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:33,500
Now I see.

4
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:35,958
That's why you
brought me here...

5
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:37,583
...to the Phantom.

6
00:02:27,166 --> 00:02:29,125
[footsteps]

7
00:02:29,208 --> 00:02:36,916
[KAZUYA panting]

8
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,541
Is Sophie in there?

9
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:40,708
It's so big!

10
00:02:40,791 --> 00:02:42,833
--[thumping]
--[PORTER A] What the hell?!

11
00:02:42,916 --> 00:02:44,083
[PORTER B]
What is it?

12
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:46,625
[PORTER A] This... trunk
has a mind of its own!

13
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,666
[PORTERS scream]

14
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:50,541
[sighs] I'm alive!

15
00:02:50,625 --> 00:02:51,500
[KAZUYA]
Miss Cécile!

16
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:52,500
[CÉCILE gasps]

17
00:02:52,583 --> 00:02:53,750
Mr. Kujo!

18
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:55,250
Why were you in that trunk?

19
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,708
What's going on?

20
00:02:56,791 --> 00:02:57,958
--Do you need any help?
--[CÉCILE] She's in trouble!

21
00:02:58,041 --> 00:02:59,750
As a teacher,
I can't just stand by

22
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,208
while a student's in jeopardy!

23
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:03,541
This was my drastic
infiltration plan!

24
00:03:03,625 --> 00:03:04,541
Please, calm down.

25
00:03:04,625 --> 00:03:06,166
What student are
you talking about?

26
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,541
Who do you think?!

27
00:03:07,625 --> 00:03:09,625
Victorique, you big dummy!

28
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:12,958
[CÉCILE]
Her father called her out again.

29
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:15,333
She's inside!

30
00:03:15,416 --> 00:03:20,041
[CÉCILE grunting]

31
00:03:20,125 --> 00:03:22,375
[VICTORIQUE] You should
stay out here, Cécile.

32
00:03:22,458 --> 00:03:25,541
Don't get any closer
to this, understand?

33
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:28,083
[CÉCILE]
She sounded so different.

34
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:30,958
I know she's in danger;
I can feel it.

35
00:03:31,041 --> 00:03:32,750
But... I was stuck in here,

36
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,333
so I couldn't do
anything to help--

37
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:35,500
[gasps]

38
00:03:35,583 --> 00:03:37,541
Wait! Kujo, come back!

39
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:45,541
Thank you, Madam.
Enjoy the performance.

40
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:47,333
[KAZUYA]
Excuse me!

41
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:48,083
Huh?

42
00:03:48,166 --> 00:03:50,166
Get out of my way!

43
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:51,291
[TICKET COLLECTORS gasp]

44
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:54,291
What's his problem?

45
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:03,875
[KAZUYA]
Victorique!

46
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:05,500
Where are you?

47
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,291
[KAZUYA]
Victorique...

48
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:13,000
Don't you worry.

49
00:04:14,208 --> 00:04:16,250
[KAZUYA]
No matter where you are...

50
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:30,958
[KAZUYA] No matter what
storm might come...

51
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:33,000
...I will find you!

52
00:04:36,583 --> 00:04:37,666
[GINGER gasps]

53
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:43,375
[KAZUYA]
I promise!

54
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:55,083
[footsteps]

55
00:04:59,458 --> 00:05:00,166
[doors rattle]

56
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:01,958
[KAZUYA]
Victorique!

57
00:05:02,041 --> 00:05:03,000
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

58
00:05:04,041 --> 00:05:05,833
[KAZUYA]
Victorique!

59
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:08,666
I found you!

60
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,291
[BLOIS]
Kujo! What?!

61
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:11,500
Why are you here?

62
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,250
You really did.

63
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:14,375
You found me.

64
00:05:14,458 --> 00:05:15,458
You really did!

65
00:05:15,541 --> 00:05:17,208
[KAZUYA]
I told you!

66
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:18,625
I always will.

67
00:05:18,708 --> 00:05:20,708
Don't you forget it!

68
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:27,958
Stop there.
Come no further.

69
00:05:28,041 --> 00:05:29,125
[gasps]

70
00:05:29,208 --> 00:05:31,166
[VICTORIQUE]
I'm sorry.

71
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:32,166
I'm sorry...

72
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:33,625
[TICKET COLLECTOR A]
There he is!

73
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:34,875
Don't, Victorique!

74
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:36,208
Wait! Please!

75
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:38,083
[TICKET COLLECTOR B]
Quick! Grab him!

76
00:05:38,166 --> 00:05:41,166
Let go of me!
You don't understand!

77
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,625
Wait! Victorique!

78
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:44,708
[TICKET COLLECTOR B]
Stop struggling!

79
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:48,041
[KAZUYA]
Victorique! What are you doing?

80
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:49,208
[gasps]

81
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:51,000
Victorique!

82
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:52,833
[doors shut]

83
00:05:54,625 --> 00:05:56,708
[TICKET COLLECTOR B]
Come on!

84
00:05:56,791 --> 00:05:58,916
[KAZUYA]
Get off of me!

85
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,416
Please! I beg you!

86
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,250
[TICKET COLLECTOR B]
Shut up!

87
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:07,291
[VICTORIQUE]
Kujo...

88
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:09,875
[footsteps]

89
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:16,125
[VICTORIQUE]
Take me to him already.

90
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:18,000
Let's go.

91
00:06:18,083 --> 00:06:21,041
Marquis Albert de Blois
isn't going to wait forever.

92
00:06:28,625 --> 00:06:32,500
[MARQUIS]
At last, welcome, my daughter.

93
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:34,666
After all of these years,

94
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:37,666
it's time for your power
to be of use to me.

95
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:41,250
I've used it a lot lately.

96
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,291
But something still puzzles me.

97
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:45,833
Why is the Ministry of
the Occult only now trying

98
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:49,000
to solve Coco Rose's murder?

99
00:06:49,083 --> 00:06:51,916
have a feeling you already
know who the culprit is.

100
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,125
But you haven't been able
to track down solid proof.

101
00:06:55,208 --> 00:06:56,666
That's your current goal.

102
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:59,583
Find it and exploit the culprit.

103
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:02,000
Doing so will allow you
to achieve an even greater

104
00:07:02,083 --> 00:07:03,791
position and authority.

105
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:06,833
[VICTORIQUE] Which means
whoever in this country

106
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:09,375
has that much influence
and power...

107
00:07:09,458 --> 00:07:10,958
...is the murderer.

108
00:07:11,041 --> 00:07:13,416
They're the ones who
killed Coco Rose.

109
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,708
[MARQUIS]
Interesting.

110
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:17,833
As expected of my
beloved Gray Wolf,

111
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:20,791
your intuition is
as sharp as a knife.

112
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,458
[BLOIS]
The Coco Rose Murder.

113
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:27,000
It was Spring of 1914.

114
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:29,708
Just before the start
of the Great War.

115
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:34,125
A messenger came from France for
an audience with Queen Coco.

116
00:07:34,208 --> 00:07:36,666
At the time, she was living
in the country house,

117
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:40,125
but the King invited her to
the palace that evening.

118
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,625
[BLOIS]
And then...

119
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:48,166
[BLOIS] The queen was
found dead in her room.

120
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:50,083
Her head severed and missing.

121
00:07:51,875 --> 00:07:54,125
[BLOIS] No one had gone
in or out of her room

122
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:55,625
since her arrival.

123
00:07:55,708 --> 00:07:57,458
Except for one person--

124
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:59,625
Her husband, the King.

125
00:07:59,708 --> 00:08:03,666
But, of course, he didn't have
anything suspicious with him.

126
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:06,833
He couldn't have
been the culprit...

127
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:07,958
...because something happened

128
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:10,458
at the country house
at that same time.

129
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:12,625
[NOBLES gasp]

130
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:21,208
[BLOIS] And someone from
the Academy of Sciences

131
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:23,000
was among the witnesses.

132
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:28,041
[BLOIS] After that,
the case just stopped.

133
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:32,166
[KAZUYA] Why do they need
Victorique to solve the case?

134
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:34,833
[BLOIS]
I'm honestly not sure.

135
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:36,791
But...

136
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:38,625
[KAZUYA]
What is it?

137
00:08:38,708 --> 00:08:40,541
[BLOIS]
If it can't solve the case,

138
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,916
it will never go back
to the Academy with you.

139
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,166
[KAZUYA gasps]
Why in the hell not?!

140
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,000
That's what my
father has decreed.

141
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:49,333
[KAZUYA]
No way!

142
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:50,916
[BLOIS]
Calm down.

143
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,375
There hasn't been a case that
the Wolf cub couldn't solve.

144
00:08:53,458 --> 00:08:55,916
I wouldn't worry so
much if I were you.

145
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:01,750
[KAZUYA]
The fragments.

146
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:04,000
Does she have all the
fragments of chaos?

147
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:07,500
[BLOIS] Huh? She's been
provided newspaper articles,

148
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,208
and the case file from the time.

149
00:09:09,291 --> 00:09:11,958
She should have
everything she needs.

150
00:09:12,041 --> 00:09:13,708
You're wrong!
It won't be enough.

151
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:15,250
[BLOIS gasps]

152
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:16,958
[KAZUYA] Victorique probably
knows everything you could learn

153
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:18,833
from normal documentation.

154
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:21,208
Then what do you suggest we do?

155
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:22,958
[KAZUYA]
I'll go gather them.

156
00:09:23,041 --> 00:09:24,583
You'll what?

157
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:26,916
[KAZUYA]
I'm the only one who can.

158
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,583
I'll bring Victorique
the fragments she needs.

159
00:09:29,666 --> 00:09:31,166
I swear it.

160
00:09:33,375 --> 00:09:35,291
From now on,
I'm fighting, too.

161
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:36,541
I won't stand by while

162
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:38,541
Victorique is taking
this on alone.

163
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:42,250
[KAZUYA]
Be patient.

164
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,500
I'm coming!

165
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:44,583
[KAZUYA gasps]

166
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:52,916
Is that Victorique?

167
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,875
[GINGER] Cordelia was
beautiful, wasn't she?

168
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:56,000
Who was what now?

169
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:58,625
That's Cordelia Gallo.

170
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:02,916
[KAZUYA] Then the woman
in this picture...

171
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:05,333
...is Victorique's mother.

172
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:08,541
Hard to believe it's
been sixteen years

173
00:10:08,625 --> 00:10:09,916
since I last saw her.

174
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
[KAZUYA gasps]

175
00:10:11,083 --> 00:10:13,333
[GINGER]
She was one of our best dancers.

176
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:16,041
Then, she simply
vanished without a trace.

177
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:18,750
[KAZUYA]
I see.

178
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:20,666
This is where her mom worked.

179
00:10:22,208 --> 00:10:25,583
[KAZUYA] And poor Victorique
is stuck here now.

180
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:27,833
Actually... you're
not the first person

181
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,500
to notice this picture today.

182
00:10:29,583 --> 00:10:31,333
[KAZUYA gasps]

183
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:32,958
[GINGER]
There was a girl earlier.

184
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:36,083
She looked a great deal
like Cordelia, in fact.

185
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:38,541
But it couldn't have
been her, right?

186
00:10:42,625 --> 00:10:44,125
[KAZUYA]
Excuse me.

187
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:46,958
[KAZUYA gasps]

188
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:49,708
[KAZUYA]
Hold on.

189
00:10:49,791 --> 00:10:52,250
What's a picture of Queen
Coco Rose doing here?

190
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:54,000
[GINGER]
It's not her.

191
00:10:54,083 --> 00:10:56,208
That's Nicole Lulu, a dancer.

192
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:58,083
But she was a dead
ringer for the Queen.

193
00:10:58,166 --> 00:11:00,666
So much so that the regulars
starting calling her

194
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:03,083
"the Blue Rose of
Downtown" and all.

195
00:11:03,166 --> 00:11:06,208
The Blue Rose, huh.
She must have been popular.

196
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:08,541
[GINGER] Oh, they
practically worshiped her.

197
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:11,291
And she never lost
her cheery demeanor.

198
00:11:11,375 --> 00:11:15,000
But, like Cordelia,
she suddenly vanished.

199
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:24,333
[CORDELIA humming]

200
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:37,125
[humming continues]

201
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:51,208
[humming continues]

202
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:57,583
[MAN A] Quit wasting time and
solve the mystery, Wolf cub!

203
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:58,750
[VICTORIQUE]
I can't.

204
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:01,125
I don't have enough
fragments, you dolt.

205
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:03,583
[MAN A] You have all
the information you need!

206
00:12:03,666 --> 00:12:04,875
[MAN B]
I thought Gray Wolves

207
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:06,458
were supposed to
know everything.

208
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:08,333
[VICTORIQUE] Only if I
have all the fragments.

209
00:12:08,416 --> 00:12:11,416
I don't. Therefore, you're
the ones wasting time.

210
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:14,500
What are you doing?!

211
00:12:15,958 --> 00:12:17,333
[LANDLORD]
A private secretary?

212
00:12:17,416 --> 00:12:20,500
[KAZUYA]
Yes, sir. Was one hired in 1900?

213
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:23,750
I know that would have been
over twenty years ago, but--

214
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,916
[LANDLORD]
Yes, strange one, that.

215
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,791
I remember it quite clearly.

216
00:12:27,875 --> 00:12:29,375
[KAZUYA, CÉCILE gasp]

217
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:32,416
[LANDLORD] The only requirements
were blonde hair and blue eyes.

218
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:36,125
Those that qualified were
measured from head to toe.

219
00:12:36,208 --> 00:12:39,833
And after the interviews were
over, they all moved out.

220
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:41,000
Something wasn't quite right

221
00:12:41,083 --> 00:12:43,125
about the men
conducting the thing.

222
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:46,708
[CÉCILE]
So, let me get this straight.

223
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:50,458
The dancer, Nicole Lulu, goes to
that bizarre secretary interview

224
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:52,583
and then promptly
disappears without a trace?

225
00:12:52,666 --> 00:12:55,166
[KAZUYA] Yeah, it's
definitely suspicious.

226
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:57,583
We're on the right trail, we
just need to keep searching.

227
00:12:57,666 --> 00:13:01,000
Yes! For Victorique's sake,
we both must soldier on!

228
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:04,041
So, uh, you really think
she's connected to this?

229
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:06,166
Miss Downtown Blue
Rose or whatever?

230
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:07,750
Uh--

231
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:12,125
Uh... No... I'm just following
a hunch is all, a gut feeling.

232
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:14,541
Anyway, we should
get going, huh?

233
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,041
Now that you mention it.

234
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:22,875
I saw her in a horse-drawn
carriage this one time.

235
00:13:22,958 --> 00:13:24,625
Huh?

236
00:13:24,708 --> 00:13:26,083
Uh...

237
00:13:27,166 --> 00:13:29,458
[GENTLEMAN] I guess it
was about ten years ago.

238
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:32,333
She had just left the
stage for a new life.

239
00:13:34,583 --> 00:13:36,708
I heard she'd become the
mistress of some rich fellow,

240
00:13:36,791 --> 00:13:38,916
like a noble, and moved
out to the country.

241
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,916
Yes, I heard the same thing.

242
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:45,541
[OLD WOMAN B]
What? Well...

243
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:48,125
Thinking back on it, I'd say
it was around ten years

244
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:50,416
after Nicole disappeared.

245
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:57,458
She answered the secretary ad,
then became a noble's mistress?

246
00:13:57,541 --> 00:13:58,708
[CÉCILE]
Sorry, Kujo!

247
00:13:58,791 --> 00:14:00,958
Thanks for waiting!

248
00:14:01,041 --> 00:14:02,583
[KAZUYA]
You went shopping?!

249
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,916
Well, I did come all
the way down here!

250
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,708
Besides, if I didn't get
a souvenir for Sophie,

251
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:08,083
she'd wring my neck.

252
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:09,625
For... Sophie?

253
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:10,875
You mean from school?

254
00:14:10,958 --> 00:14:13,250
Yes, we come shopping
together all the time!

255
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:14,416
She'll probably be angry

256
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,125
when she finds out
I came here by myself,

257
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:18,041
but what can you do?

258
00:14:18,125 --> 00:14:19,583
So you don't know?

259
00:14:19,666 --> 00:14:22,041
Sophie's actually in
Saubreme right now.

260
00:14:22,125 --> 00:14:23,458
[CÉCILE]
Huh?

261
00:14:23,541 --> 00:14:26,000
Yeah. She brought me here
on her bike earlier today.

262
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:28,833
She said she was going to
see the big Coco Rose play.

263
00:14:28,916 --> 00:14:32,208
Huh?! Why didn't
she invite me, huh?

264
00:14:32,291 --> 00:14:34,541
Why would she abandon her
best friend of ten years

265
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:36,458
to go with you? Tell me!

266
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:38,500
You've been friend
for ten years?

267
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:40,041
That's great!
How'd you two meet?

268
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:41,958
Not telling you!

269
00:14:42,041 --> 00:14:43,125
[KAZUYA gasps]

270
00:14:43,208 --> 00:14:45,875
I hate you, Kujo!
Don't talk to me again!

271
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:47,291
Oh, come on.

272
00:14:47,375 --> 00:14:49,625
--Don't be like that.
--And I hate Sophie even more!

273
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:52,666
That traitor!

274
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:55,541
[SOPHIE sneezes, groans]

275
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:58,500
I better not be catching a cold.

276
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:00,083
Aah... Oh, well.

277
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:03,291
As long as I get to see
Coco, it's worth it!

278
00:15:03,375 --> 00:15:04,833
[BAKER]
Nicole Lulu?

279
00:15:04,916 --> 00:15:07,416
I heard you were a fan and
thought you could help us.

280
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:09,250
I was. And my heart's
still broken,

281
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:12,500
even after all of these years.
I can't believe she's dead.

282
00:15:12,583 --> 00:15:13,416
[BOTH gasp]

283
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,458
[BAKER gasps]

284
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:18,333
Wow, you two really
are clueless.

285
00:15:18,416 --> 00:15:20,166
Nicole's long dead.

286
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:24,458
[KAZUYA]
He's right.

287
00:15:26,666 --> 00:15:29,166
[CÉCILE]
It says she passed away in 1900!

288
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:31,583
[KAZUYA]
Can't be.

289
00:15:31,666 --> 00:15:34,375
That's the year she was
supposed to have gone missing.

290
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:37,708
Right after they recruited
for a private secretary.

291
00:15:37,791 --> 00:15:39,208
You're right!

292
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:42,583
And those women said they
saw her ten years after that!

293
00:15:44,916 --> 00:15:50,958
[bell ringing]

294
00:15:51,041 --> 00:15:54,583
[VICTORIQUE groaning]

295
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:01,875
[BLOIS]
Put an end to this, Father.

296
00:16:01,958 --> 00:16:03,750
Nothing good is coming of it.

297
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:06,166
[MARQUIS]
Oh, ye of little faith.

298
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,666
Watch your sister
carefully, Grévil.

299
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:11,166
Her true power will
leave you in awe.

300
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,541
[phone clicks]

301
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:14,958
[BLOIS]
Wait, Father! Listen to me!

302
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:17,166
[VICTORIQUE chuckles]

303
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:18,666
[BLOIS gasps]

304
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,083
[VICTORIQUE] They've employed
a blend of specific herbs

305
00:16:20,166 --> 00:16:21,583
that hone the senses.

306
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:24,000
The monotonous ringing and
the flicker of the candle light

307
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:28,000
do little more than enhance
the effects of the smoke.

308
00:16:28,083 --> 00:16:30,041
There's nothing
occult about this.

309
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:34,333
In the end... even our
father must rely on science.

310
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:40,958
[CÉCILE]
The tickets are sold out,

311
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:42,958
and there are guards everywhere.

312
00:16:43,041 --> 00:16:45,333
How are we supposed
to get inside, Kujo?

313
00:16:45,416 --> 00:16:48,833
Inspector Blois should be
coming any minute now.

314
00:16:48,916 --> 00:16:50,500
[MAN A]
Who's the culprit?

315
00:16:50,583 --> 00:16:53,000
[MAN B]
Solve the mystery, Gray Wolf!

316
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,625
[MAN D] No one is allowed
to leave this room

317
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:00,500
until the ritual is complete.

318
00:17:00,583 --> 00:17:03,125
[BLOIS grunts, growls]

319
00:17:03,208 --> 00:17:05,583
Think you've been had.

320
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:15,375
[gasps]

321
00:17:15,458 --> 00:17:17,791
Come on, Miss Cécile! This way!

322
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:21,458
[CÉCILE gasps]
Kujo, wait! Where are you going?

323
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:24,458
[yelps]

324
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:35,166
[VICTORIQUE groaning]

325
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:38,458
[MAN A]
Cooperate! Solve the mystery!

326
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:39,625
[MAN B]
Hurry!

327
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:41,208
[MAN C]
Who is the murderer?

328
00:17:41,291 --> 00:17:44,708
[MAN D]
How did they kill Coco Rose?

329
00:17:44,791 --> 00:17:46,041
[MAN D]
We know you have the power!

330
00:17:46,125 --> 00:17:47,083
[MAN A]
Stop wasting our time!

331
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:48,958
[MAN B]
Use your talents, Gray Wolf.

332
00:17:49,041 --> 00:17:51,750
[MAN C]
Solve it! Solve it and it ends!

333
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:53,041
[BLOIS grunts]

334
00:17:59,375 --> 00:18:01,375
[KAZUYA grunts]

335
00:18:01,458 --> 00:18:03,541
[ROSCOE]
What's wrong?

336
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:05,541
What happened to all
that self-confidence

337
00:18:05,625 --> 00:18:07,708
you showed me before...

338
00:18:07,791 --> 00:18:08,791
...little boy?

339
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:10,250
Why are you here--

340
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:14,041
[MAN B]
Stop being stubborn!

341
00:18:14,125 --> 00:18:15,250
[MAN C]
Solve the mystery!

342
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:16,541
[BLOIS]
Leave her alone--

343
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:27,041
[MAN B]
What's going on?

344
00:18:27,125 --> 00:18:28,875
[MAN A]
Get the lights! Hurry!

345
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:36,708
[gasps]

346
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,791
Brian Roscoe...

347
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:53,375
[GUARD groans]

348
00:18:55,041 --> 00:18:56,166
[ROSCOE]
Hurry up.

349
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:58,000
The cub is through
the door back there.

350
00:18:58,083 --> 00:18:59,125
[gasps]

351
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:02,666
[KAZUYA]
Thanks!

352
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:07,958
[KAZUYA]
Victorique! Victorique!

353
00:19:08,041 --> 00:19:10,583
Victorique! Victorique!

354
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:11,666
Victorique!

355
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,416
[BLOIS gasps]

356
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,791
Kujo!

357
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:16,541
That man...

358
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:25,500
How can you be in here?!

359
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,041
[KAZUYA gasps]
Victorique!

360
00:19:50,125 --> 00:19:51,375
Are you okay?

361
00:19:51,458 --> 00:19:52,541
Answer me!

362
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:54,083
Victorique!

363
00:20:01,583 --> 00:20:04,333
[VICTORIQUE groans]

364
00:20:06,875 --> 00:20:08,291
[VICTORIQUE]
Kujo?

365
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:10,083
I'm so glad.

366
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:11,833
You're okay...

367
00:20:11,916 --> 00:20:13,291
You're okay.

368
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:14,666
Thank goodness.

369
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,250
You don't understand!
This case is too--

370
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:19,708
[KAZUYA]
I know!

371
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:23,541
Believe me, I know.

372
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:25,625
You didn't want me
to get involved.

373
00:20:25,708 --> 00:20:27,041
That's why...

374
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:28,916
You...

375
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,041
...left me.

376
00:20:31,125 --> 00:20:32,583
You had to.

377
00:20:35,208 --> 00:20:37,666
[KAZUYA]
But I did get involved.

378
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:39,416
And that's okay.

379
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:42,416
I'm your friend and
a busybody, remember?

380
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,916
So you'll always have...

381
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,625
You'll always have someone
who will get involved for you.

382
00:20:47,708 --> 00:20:49,750
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

383
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,375
Kujo...

384
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:54,708
[MAN A] The sacred
ritual's been disturbed!

385
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:56,333
[MAN B]
Throw that boy out of here!

386
00:20:56,416 --> 00:20:57,916
[BLOIS]
Stop right there!

387
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:06,916
Kujo.

388
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,375
Huh?

389
00:21:08,458 --> 00:21:10,875
[VICTORIQUE] We can continue
to struggle against this.

390
00:21:10,958 --> 00:21:13,750
But nothing we do will free
me from my father's curse.

391
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:15,375
Hold on.

392
00:21:15,458 --> 00:21:17,125
Solve the mystery.

393
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:18,291
[gasps]

394
00:21:21,666 --> 00:21:23,541
Solve the mystery...

395
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:25,375
...in order to survive.

396
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:28,875
[CODELIA, VICTORIQUE]
I'll show them my power.

397
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:32,875
[grunting]

398
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,416
[VICTORIQUE]
I'll solve it!

399
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:37,666
[VICTORIQUE]
That's what you want, right?

400
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:41,791
The mystery of Coco Rose's
murder won't stay that way.

401
00:21:48,583 --> 00:21:52,208
[MARQUIS] To the beautiful
Wolf mother and her cub...

402
00:21:52,291 --> 00:21:54,541
...I give this blessing.

403
00:21:57,291 --> 00:21:59,541
[VICTORIQUE]
Kujo...

404
00:21:59,625 --> 00:22:01,000
What made you, of all people,

405
00:22:01,083 --> 00:22:03,500
think to investigate
Nicole Lulu's case?

406
00:22:03,583 --> 00:22:04,458
[KAZUYA gasps]

407
00:22:04,541 --> 00:22:06,333
Not sure, really.

408
00:22:06,416 --> 00:22:08,250
Probably...

409
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:10,958
...because I thought the
story would make you happy.

410
00:22:12,458 --> 00:22:15,416
I'll admit, for a dull honor
student, that was good thinking.

411
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,333
Well done.

412
00:22:16,416 --> 00:22:18,000
[KAZUYA gasps]

413
00:22:19,208 --> 00:22:20,541
[footsteps]

414
00:22:20,625 --> 00:22:22,833
[BLOIS] I received my
father's permission.

415
00:22:25,083 --> 00:22:27,291
Now then... Where are we going?

416
00:22:27,375 --> 00:22:28,041
[VICTORIQUE]
The graveyard.

417
00:22:28,125 --> 00:22:29,458
The what?

418
00:22:29,541 --> 00:22:31,250
You heard what I said.

419
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,958
We're digging up
Nicole Lulu's grave.

420
00:24:15,208 --> 00:24:16,708
[KAZUYA]
The curtain will finally go up

421
00:24:16,791 --> 00:24:19,708
on Coco Rose's last performance.

422
00:24:19,791 --> 00:24:21,791
[VICTORIQUE]
Coco, I'll lay a special bouquet

423
00:24:21,875 --> 00:24:23,541
upon the story of your life...

424
00:24:23,625 --> 00:24:26,333
...made with the flowers
of falsehood and truth...

425
00:24:26,416 --> 00:24:29,250
...that can only
bloom within chaos.

